
                                            The African National Congress leadership in KwaZulu-Natal discusses the outcomes of its talks with the party’s top six.
                                         DURBAN - The African National Congress (ANC) leadership in KwaZulu-Natal discuss the outcomes of its talks with the party’s top six. Senior officials led by President Jacob Zuma met with factions over the past few days in an effort to foster unity following a court judgment which nullified the KZN executive. 